If it results in &quot;This page can&#39;t be reached&quot;. It means that &quot;too many redirects&quot;. So you need to modify the rule to avoid the infinite loop. 


you could use below URL rewrite rule:

 

    &lt;rule name=&quot;HTTP to HTTPS1&quot; enabled=&quot;true&quot; stopProcessing=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
     &lt;match url=&quot;(.*)&quot; /&gt;
     &lt;conditions&gt;
         &lt;add input=&quot;{HTTPS}&quot; pattern=&quot;off&quot; /&gt;
     &lt;/conditions&gt;
     &lt;action type=&quot;Redirect&quot; url=&quot;https://{HTTP_HOST}{REQUEST_URI}&quot; appendQueryString=&quot;false&quot; redirectType=&quot;Permanent&quot; /&gt;
     &lt;/rule&gt;


{REQUEST_URI} contains URL&#39;s path, including the query string with a leading slash.

also check your iis site binding with Http and https. make sure you bind the correct certificate.


you could use below PowerShell command to create a self-signed certificate:

    New-SelfSignedCertificate -DnsName www.sample1.com -CertStoreLocation cert:Localmachine\My


and move that certificate to trusted root folder.


